DESCRIPTION:As part of this summer’s Kicking It at Hermann Park offerings\,
	 enjoy “Moonlight Movie Nights\,” presented by Goya\, in the Commons! On S
	aturday\, June 20\, join us for a showing of A Bug’s Life (1998 | G | 1h 3
	5m runtime). \nThe movie will start at approximately 8:30 p.m.\, around su
	nset. The movie showing is free and open to the public. \nBe sure to get t
	o the Commons early to snag your spot on the lawn. Guests are welcome to b
	ring blankets or lawn chairs to settle in for the movie. \nFood and bevera
	ge will be available for purchase at the cafe and with food vendors on-sit
	e. \nThank you to Goya for their generous support!\n\nhttps://hermannpark.
	org/event/moonlight-movie-nights-the-parent-trap-2/\n\nFrom Hermann Park C
	onservancy
